f-clock
=======

Time encoder/decoder using prime factorization.
(ACM Mini Coding Challenge: Code the worst way to tell time in 1 hour)

SYNOPSIS
--------
```
python f-clock.py [-v]
```

DESCRIPTION
-----------
Encodes current time (HHMMSS) as products of large primes. Each digit (0-9)
gets mapped to a ~128-bit composite number by selecting N random primes from
a pool of first 70 primes, where N equals the digit value.

Decodes via factorization.

OPTIONS
-------
  -v, --verbose Print encoding/decoding details, otherwise just encoded numbers.

ALGORITHM
---------
- Pool: First 70 primes (2..349)
- encoder(d): Select d + 1 primes, adjust exponents to hit ~128 bits
- decoder(n): Factorize, count distinct primes from pool and subtract 1 = original digit

EXAMPLE
-------
```
$ python f-clock.py
248187293863347975401129272743132504001
5983127612737891438490297376702478583552
513230455327656227499061920163813355701
1887701754357656323188057196765825439557
12268194810095027807998688349789677233369
972786042517719014174576083150881262357
----------------------------------------------------------------------
```

